a quick way to
access normal mode command
from insert mode

why?
- efficient
- control undo point
- control ctrl-u behaviour

how?
- alt or meta key + normal mode command
- ctrl-o

it's showtime!

the weird alt-a

suggestion
" Ref: https://vi.stackexchange.com/a/2363/34851
if !has('nvim') | execute "set <M-a>=\ea" | endif
inoremap <M-a> <C-o>a

endslide
